    <item>
      <title>Resolving NGINX 502 Bad Gateway Errors After OS Upgrade</title>
      <link>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/resolve-nginx-502-bad-gateway-errors-os-upgrade/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 22 Jun 2026 08:23:51 &#43;0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/resolve-nginx-502-bad-gateway-errors-os-upgrade/</guid>
      <description>The NGINX 502 Bad Gateway error typically occurs when there&amp;rsquo;s an issue with the server acting as a gateway or proxy, often due to configuration problems or server overload. To resolve this error after an OS upgrade, review your server configuration and ensure that all services are properly restarted and configured.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Troubleshooting NGINX Bad Gateway Errors: A Comprehensive Guide</title>
      <link>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/nginx-bad-gateway-error-troubleshooting/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 16:23:51 &#43;0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/nginx-bad-gateway-error-troubleshooting/</guid>
      <description>To check and fix a bad gateway error in NGINX, inspect the server logs, verify the upstream server configuration, and ensure proper communication between NGINX and the upstream server. Common issues include incorrect proxy_pass directives, server overload, and network connectivity problems.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Diagnose and Fix 502 Bad Gateway Errors in NGINX</title>
